<h3 class="ui header">Ember CLI Preloader</h3>
  <p>Displays a preloader that is visible while the browser is evaluating your JavaScript. This example uses the default preloader (packaged with ember-cli-preloader).</p>

<h3 class="ui header">Customizing the preloader's HTML and CSS</h3>
  <p>
    Running <code class="inline">ember install ember-cli-preloader</code> adds these files to your project: <br>
    <b>- app/preloader/preloader.html</b><br>
    <b>- app/preloader/preloader.css</b>
  </p>
  <p>See the {{link-to 'Documentation' 'docs'}} on how to configure the name/location for your preloader's HTML and CSS.</p>

  <!--<code class="code-example" data-gist-id="84d1884c897f15c0d87d"></code>-->
