  <p>And after the DOM is rendered, the default behavior is to immediately remove the preloader's HTML and CSS from the index.html. However, depending on your preloader, that may be too abrupt and look ugly.</p>
  <p>See the {{link-to 'Documentation' 'docs'}} on how to configure the behavior for removing your preloader <i>(adding a delay and/or 'loaded' class)</i>.</p>
  <!--<p>You can configure this behavior from your <b>config/environment.js</b> file.</p>-->


<h3>Configurable</h3>
  <ul class="ui list">
    <li>Where the preloader HTML/CSS is loaded from (<i>ember-cli-build.js</i>)</li>
    <li>Add a class once DOM is rendered or whenever you feel like via the preloader service.</li>
    <li>Remove preloader HTML/CSS once DOM is rendered or whenever you feel like via the preloader service.</li>
    <li>Add a delay for removal of your preloader (good for fade-out effects) (<i>config/environment.js</i>).</li>
  </ul>
